###
### Job Marketplace API - Test Collection
### Base URL: http://localhost:3000
###  Test the API
Open http://localhost:3000/api for Swagger documentation

### Variables
@baseUrl = http://localhost:3000
@hirerToken = YOUR_HIRER_ACCESS_TOKEN
@hustlerToken = YOUR_HUSTLER_ACCESS_TOKEN
@jobId = JOB_ID
@hustlerId = HUSTLER_USER_ID
@applicationId =APPLICATION_ID

### ============================================
### AUTHENTICATION
### ============================================

### 1. Register Hirer
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "John Hirer",
  "email": "hirer@test.com",
  "password": "password123",
  "role": "hirer"
}

### 2. Register Hustler
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Jane Hustler",
  "email": "hustler@test.com",
  "password": "password123",
  "role": "hustler"
}

### 3. Login as Hirer
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "hirer@test.com",
  "password": "password123"
}

### 4. Login as Hustler
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "hustler@test.com",
  "password": "password123"
}

### 5. Get Current User (Hirer)
GET {{baseUrl}}/auth/me
Authorization: Bearer {{hirerToken}}

### 6. Get Current User (Hustler)
GET {{baseUrl}}/auth/me
Authorization: Bearer {{hustlerToken}}

### 7. Refresh Token
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/refresh-token
Authorization: Bearer {{hirerToken}}

### 8. Reset Password
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/reset-password
Authorization: Bearer {{hirerToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "oldPassword": "password123",
  "newPassword": "newpassword123"
}

### 9. Logout
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/logout
Authorization: Bearer {{hirerToken}}

### ============================================
### JOBS (Hirer Endpoints)
### ============================================

### 10. Create Job (Hirer only)
POST {{baseUrl}}/jobs
Authorization: Bearer {{hirerToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "title": "Full Stack Developer Needed",
  "description": "Looking for an experienced full stack developer to build a web application with React and Node.js. Must have experience with MongoDB and REST APIs.",
  "budget": 5000,
  "requiredSkills": ["React", "Node.js", "MongoDB", "TypeScript", "REST APIs"]
}

### 11. Get All Open Jobs (Any authenticated user)
GET {{baseUrl}}/jobs
Authorization: Bearer {{hustlerToken}}

### 12. Get My Jobs (Hirer only)
GET {{baseUrl}}/jobs/my-jobs
Authorization: Bearer {{hirerToken}}

### 13. Get Job by ID
GET {{baseUrl}}/jobs/{{jobId}}
Authorization: Bearer {{hirerToken}}

### 14. Update Job (Hirer only, own jobs)
PATCH {{baseUrl}}/jobs/{{jobId}}
Authorization: Bearer {{hirerToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "title": "Senior Full Stack Developer Needed",
  "budget": 6000
}

### 15. Delete Job (Hirer only, own jobs)
DELETE {{baseUrl}}/jobs/{{jobId}}
Authorization: Bearer {{hirerToken}}

### 16. Select Best Candidate (Hirer only)
POST {{baseUrl}}/jobs/{{jobId}}/select-candidate/{{hustlerId}}
Authorization: Bearer {{hirerToken}}

### 17. Close Job (Hirer only)
POST {{baseUrl}}/jobs/{{jobId}}/close
Authorization: Bearer {{hirerToken}}

### ============================================
### APPLICATIONS (Hustler/Hirer Endpoints)
### ============================================

### 18. Apply to Job (Hustler only)
### NOTE: Use Postman or Thunder Client for file upload
### Or use curl:
### curl -X POST http://localhost:3000/applications/job/{{jobId}} \
###   -H "Authorization: Bearer {{hustlerToken}}" \
###   -F "message=I have 5 years of experience in full stack development..." \
###   -F "expectedCost=4500" \
###   -F "file=@/path/to/your/resume.pdf"

POST {{baseUrl}}/applications/job/{{jobId}}
Authorization: Bearer {{hustlerToken}}
Content-Type: multipart/form-data; boundary=----WebKitFormBoundary7MA4YWxkTrZu0gW

------WebKitFormBoundary7MA4YWxkTrZu0gW
Content-Disposition: form-data; name="message"

I have 5 years of experience in full stack development with React, Node.js, and MongoDB. I have built multiple web applications and REST APIs. I am confident I can deliver this project within the timeline and budget.
------WebKitFormBoundary7MA4YWxkTrZu0gW
Content-Disposition: form-data; name="expectedCost"

4500
------WebKitFormBoundary7MA4YWxkTrZu0gW
Content-Disposition: form-data; name="file"; filename="resume.pdf"
Content-Type: application/pdf

< ./test-files/sample-resume.pdf
------WebKitFormBoundary7MA4YWxkTrZu0gW--

### 19. Get Applications for a Job (Hirer only, own jobs)
GET {{baseUrl}}/applications/job/{{jobId}}
Authorization: Bearer {{hirerToken}}

### 20. Get My Applications (Hustler only)
GET {{baseUrl}}/applications/my-applications
Authorization: Bearer {{hustlerToken}}

### 21. Update Application Status - Accept (Hirer only)
PATCH {{baseUrl}}/applications/{{applicationId}}/status/accepted
Authorization: Bearer {{hirerToken}}

### 22. Update Application Status - Reject (Hirer only)
PATCH {{baseUrl}}/applications/{{applicationId}}/status/rejected
Authorization: Bearer {{hirerToken}}

### 23. Delete Application (Hustler only, own pending applications)
DELETE {{baseUrl}}/applications/{{applicationId}}
Authorization: Bearer {{hustlerToken}}

### ============================================
### COMPLETE WORKFLOW TEST
### ============================================

### Step 1: Register and login as Hirer
### Step 2: Create a job and copy the job ID
### Step 3: Register and login as Hustler
### Step 4: View available jobs
### Step 5: Apply to the job with a file
### Step 6: Login as Hirer again
### Step 7: View applications for your job
### Step 8: Select the best candidate
### Step 9: Check job status updated to "in_progress"

### ============================================
### NOTES
### ============================================

# For file uploads, use tools like:
# - Postman
# - Thunder Client (VS Code extension)
# - Insomnia
# - curl command line

# Example curl for file upload:
# curl -X POST http://localhost:3000/applications/job/YOUR_JOB_ID \
#   -H "Authorization: Bearer YOUR_TOKEN" \
#   -F "message=Your message here" \
#   -F "expectedCost=4500" \
#   -F "file=@/path/to/resume.pdf"
